 in the rest of the 50 m deep mixed layer. Frontogenetic\nmechanisms are diagnosed through analysis of the transport equation for squared\nbuoyancy gradient. Horizontal strain is the primary frontogenetic term and is\ncounteracted primarily by horizontal diffusion in the top 10 m and by the\nhorizontal gradient of vertical velocity further below.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 16 Oct 2019 21:33:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-18"}
